CBIGene:6607"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "Smon/c", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.7829679846763611, "span": {"begin": 671, "end": 677}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "mutants", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.5426400303840637, "span": {"begin": 865, "end": 872}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:6469"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "SHH", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9965454936027527, "span": {"begin": 952, "end": 955}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "explant", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.5703125596046448, "span": {"begin": 1045, "end": 1052}}], "text": "In vitro     None identified      In vivo      To investigate how SHH might regulate early pharyngeal arch (PA1) development SHH-/- embryos were generated. At E9.5, the mutant embryos were thinner with hypoplasia on PA1. Morphometrics of PA1 of mutant vs. control showed a significant decrease in size in the mutant (P&lt;0.05) for both the dorsal-ventral and the anteroposterior axis. Hypoplasia was quantified using a Pax3-Cre/R26R transgenic mouse line marked with LacZ and stained with X-gal (Yamagishi, Yamagishi et al. 2006).    SHH expressed in thickened palatal epithelium prior to palatal shelf outgrowth (E13.0-14.5) (Rice, Connor et al. 2006)   Using Wnt1-Cre;Smon/c embryos, a significant decrease in the growth of the mandibular arch in both the proximodistal and dorsoventral (D-V) axes. This supports that observation that the wild type, but not the mutants undergo rapid growth in the D-V axis around E11.5 (Jeong, Mao et al. 2004).    SHH is expressed in oral epithelium and shown as a key signal for palatal shelf outgrowth in explant culture (Lan and Jiang 2009)", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:50:20 +0000 2026"}